\color none
Collecting terms we have 
\begin_inset Formula $\nu_{\tau+1}=\frac{1-a_{\tau}-b_{\rho}}{b_{\rho}}(A_{\tau}(1+r)+\delta_{\tau+1}-\nu_{\tau+1})$
\end_inset

, 
\begin_inset Formula $\nu_{\tau+1}\frac{(1-a_{\tau})}{b_{\rho}}=\frac{1-a_{\tau}-b_{\rho}}{b_{\rho}}(A_{\tau}(1+r)+\delta_{\tau+1})$
\end_inset


\end_layout

\end_inset

: 
\begin_inset Formula 
\begin{alignat*}{1}
\nu_{\tau+1} & =\frac{(1+r)(1-a_{\tau}-b_{\rho})}{1-a_{\tau}}A_{t}+\frac{(1-a_{\tau}-b_{\rho})}{1-a_{\tau}}\delta_{\tau+1}
\end{alignat*}

\end_inset


\end_layout

\begin_layout Standard
Further, denoting the disposable income 
\begin_inset Formula $\delta_{t}=i_{t}-\Psi_{t}$
\end_inset

 and using the first-order conditions in the equation 
\begin_inset CommandInset ref
LatexCommand ref
reference "eq:mar2020_euler"
plural "false"
caps "false"
noprefix "false"

\end_inset

, we rewrite the Euler equations as follows:
\end_layout

